Our Secret
EP07

2
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:44,759
Siyue

3
00:01:45,039 --> 00:01:47,360
Let's play billiards this Sunday.

4
00:01:48,190 --> 00:01:48,950
What are you planning?

5
00:01:49,229 --> 00:01:50,160
Count me in.

6
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,270
I'll think about it.

7
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:53,120
The math competition is approaching.

8
00:01:54,509 --> 00:01:56,000
Xianxian, you can join us.

9
00:01:56,190 --> 00:01:58,039
I can't play billiards.

10
00:01:58,229 --> 00:01:59,440
Neither can I.

11
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,120
Anyway,

12
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:03,230
you just aim at the billiard ball and poke it.

13
00:02:04,310 --> 00:02:05,800
That's so embarrassing. I don't want to go with you.

14
00:02:05,950 --> 00:02:06,910
Oh my!

15
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,910
I don't want to go with you, either.

16
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,670
Well, let's go with them.

17
00:02:16,270 --> 00:02:17,550
I can teach you how to play billiards.

18
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:21,320
Yeah!

19
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,520
How about asking Jiang Chen to join us?

20
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,470
Forget it.

21
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:28,550
He's too good at it. We don't want to embarrass ourselves.

22
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:32,110
If you can't see clearly, just tell me.

23
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:49,190
I can take the notes for you.

24
00:02:49,630 --> 00:02:51,829
You need to focus on your competition paper.

25
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,750
I can finish it on time.

26
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:04,910
Dinner is ready.

27
00:03:05,910 --> 00:03:06,270
I'm coming.

28
00:03:06,270 --> 00:03:07,440
Hurry up.

29
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:15,440
Here you are.

30
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:19,750
Mom

31
00:03:20,270 --> 00:03:22,240
I want to discuss something with you.

32
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:27,030
I want to change a pair of stronger glasses.

33
00:03:27,670 --> 00:03:28,960
Your nearsightedness has gotten worse?

34
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:30,720
Yeah.

35
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:34,550
Xianxian, it was just pseudo myopia before.

36
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:36,190
Wearing glasses is to correct visual acuity.

37
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,190
How could it get worse?

38
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:41,470
I have no idea. I can't see clearly sometimes.

39
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:43,720
Which row of seats are you in now?

40
00:03:45,750 --> 00:03:46,910
The fifth one.

41
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,440
Then you can talk to your teacher

42
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:50,390
to move your seat to the front row.

43
00:03:51,630 --> 00:03:52,750
You'd better

44
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:54,440
not depend too much on glasses.

45
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:56,320
If your nearsightedness keeps getting worse,

46
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:58,600
you have to wear glasses all the time.

47
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,080
If you don't want to talk to the teacher yourself,

48
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,320
I can talk to him about it.

49
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:06,880
No. Forget it.

50
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:11,190
You dad told me that

51
00:04:11,830 --> 00:04:13,880
the science-arts division is coming.

52
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:16,350
It comes just in time.

53
00:04:16,510 --> 00:04:18,200
When you are in the arts class,

54
00:04:18,390 --> 00:04:19,230
you can sit in the front row.

55
00:04:19,390 --> 00:04:20,320
All will be settled then.

56
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:23,760
But I may choose science, too.

57
00:04:29,790 --> 00:04:31,920
You are a girl. How can you learn science?

58
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:35,640
Why can't girls learn science?

59
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:37,920
I don't mean that girls can't learn science.

60
00:04:38,230 --> 00:04:40,510
It's just girls are usually not good at learning science courses.

61
00:04:42,270 --> 00:04:42,880
You must think that

62
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:45,040
there is little difference between your academic performance on the two courses.

63
00:04:45,230 --> 00:04:47,640
The science courses will be much more difficult in the junior and senior years.

64
00:04:48,510 --> 00:04:48,880
But ......

65
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:50,830
That's enough.

66
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,350
I have made the decision for you. Choose the arts class.

67
00:04:54,070 --> 00:04:55,320
How can you say that?

68
00:04:55,950 --> 00:04:57,790
This is my own business.

69
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:00,110
Don't I have the right to

70
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:01,350
make my own choice?

71
00:05:01,550 --> 00:05:03,670
You don't know how to make a better choice.

72
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:07,760
I'm only telling you this for your own good!

73
00:05:07,950 --> 00:05:09,670
And you dad can help you with the courses.

74
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,040
So you can go to a better college.

75
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:14,040
We did this all

76
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,510
for your own good!

77
00:05:16,670 --> 00:05:18,230
Stop arguing with me.

78
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,230
That's enough.

79
00:05:19,510 --> 00:05:21,200
Calm down.

80
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:23,230
It is a very big deal.

81
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:25,720
We should talk it over.

82
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,320
Xianxian

83
00:05:29,230 --> 00:05:30,880
Don't talk to your mom like that!

84
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:37,920
I'm full.

85
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:48,070
You can't educate children like that.

86
00:05:48,230 --> 00:05:49,320
You are good at educating.

87
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:50,830
You really did a good job,

88
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:53,320
and she just left the table like that.

89
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:07,480
Xianxian, come online quickly.

90
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,830
Accept my friend request online.

91
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:23,110
Welcome Little Monster.

92
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:40,110
Put down your cell phone and do your homework carefully.

93
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:46,350
Xianxian

94
00:06:48,790 --> 00:06:51,390
You told mom that you want a phone

95
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:53,230
a few days ago.

96
00:06:54,230 --> 00:06:55,600
And we bought you

97
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,159
this one.

98
00:07:00,830 --> 00:07:01,950
What's wrong?

99
00:07:05,070 --> 00:07:06,350
Sorry, dad.

100
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:10,640
I lied to you.

101
00:07:11,790 --> 00:07:12,950
About what?

102
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:27,390
Zhou Siyue lent me this.

103
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:30,510
I saw it this morning.

104
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,550
Well,

105
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,760
just return it

106
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,550
to him later.

107
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,640
Xianxian

108
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,350
Since we have bought you this mobile phone,

109
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:46,390
I'd like to make some rules for you.

110
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,640
First,

111
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:51,000
don't bring the phone to school.

112
00:07:51,159 --> 00:07:52,200
It will distract you.

113
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:55,200
Second,

114
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:58,790
I hope you can think about

115
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,110
what your mom said to you just now.

116
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:04,440
She had a point there.

117
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:10,040
Dad, you also think

118
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,200
I should choose arts?

119
00:08:16,110 --> 00:08:18,200
I have the same idea as your mother.

120
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,950
It's just that girls may suffer more

121
00:08:21,110 --> 00:08:22,670
to learn science courses.

122
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,790
And we don't want you to go through this.

123
00:08:25,230 --> 00:08:26,640
How about you, dad?

124
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:29,000
Why did you choose to major in politics?

125
00:08:29,390 --> 00:08:30,110
Me?

126
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:35,280
I was not good at science courses.

127
00:08:35,549 --> 00:08:37,080
And it shows exactly that

128
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,960
girls are good at arts courses

129
00:08:39,110 --> 00:08:40,400
while boys are good at science courses

130
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,590
is not a correct theory.

131
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:47,640
By the way,

132
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:50,840
I get angry not because you don't want me to learn science.

133
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,280
I'm angry because you don't let me make the choice myself.

134
00:09:01,150 --> 00:09:02,230
Xianxian

135
00:09:02,790 --> 00:09:04,710
We did this because

136
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:07,280
we are afraid that you will make a wrong choice

137
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:10,080
and can't bear the consequences it may cause.

138
00:09:13,030 --> 00:09:16,030
If you've made your determination,

139
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:18,470
I'll

140
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,960
respect your decision.

141
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,030
Thank you, dad.

142
00:09:31,470 --> 00:09:32,470
And, yeah,

143
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:35,320
don't be angry with your mother anymore.

144
00:09:35,520 --> 00:09:36,640
Her bark is worse than her bite.

145
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:37,880
You know that.

146
00:09:38,150 --> 00:09:39,230
And

147
00:09:39,550 --> 00:09:43,230
I think she may be going through menopause.

148
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,470
Okay.

149
00:09:46,910 --> 00:09:48,520
I'm not mad at her anymore.

150
00:09:50,470 --> 00:09:51,150
Honey.

151
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,400
You may do your homework now.

152
00:10:12,880 --> 00:10:14,110
Hello, senior.

153
00:10:15,110 --> 00:10:16,550
Could you please do me a favor

154
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:18,400
to give me some exercises and materials

155
00:10:18,590 --> 00:10:20,080
of science for junior students?

156
00:10:23,350 --> 00:10:25,550
This is the composition topic of this year's college entrance examination.

157
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,640
Finish it

158
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:29,590
in two classes.

159
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:59,150
These are exercises of science for junior students.

160
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:04,230
It's not that difficult.

161
00:11:04,710 --> 00:11:05,840
Yeah.

162
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:09,440
I can handle all these now.

163
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:11,550
If I choose science

164
00:11:12,230 --> 00:11:13,350
and work very hard,

165
00:11:14,230 --> 00:11:16,200
maybe I can get better grades than you.

166
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,350
Miss...

167
00:11:26,710 --> 00:11:27,880
What are you doing?

168
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:29,470
I've finished the composition.

169
00:11:34,880 --> 00:11:35,960
Come to my office

170
00:11:36,150 --> 00:11:37,760
before the noon self-study course.

171
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,280
Your composition is pretty good.

172
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:54,000
Your writing skills are not bad.

173
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:58,150
You'll choose the science class?

174
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,520
Mr. Liu

175
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:04,230
What's the matter with these girls of your class?

176
00:12:04,710 --> 00:12:07,470
Kong Shadi said she wanted to choose the science class yesterday.

177
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,640
And so does her.

178
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,200
Have you handed in your application form for the science-arts division?

179
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,030
Not yet.

180
00:12:15,230 --> 00:12:16,080
Think it twice.

181
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:17,760
May I come in?

182
00:12:17,910 --> 00:12:18,670
Yes, please.

183
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:20,880
Mr. Liu

184
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:22,670
I want to participate in the math competition, too.

185
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:24,840
The Placement Test is about to come.

186
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:25,760
Can you handle all these?

187
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:27,440
Chinese is a very important lesson.

188
00:12:27,470 --> 00:12:28,520
He Xingwen

189
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:31,280
Attending the competition is not the only way to go to a good college.

190
00:12:31,590 --> 00:12:32,790
Your academic performance of all courses

191
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,470
is pretty good.

192
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,960
You can go to a good college by attending the college entrance examination.

193
00:12:37,280 --> 00:12:38,550
Zhou Siyue can participate in the competition.

194
00:12:38,880 --> 00:12:39,960
My academic performance is better than his.

195
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:41,640
Why can't I participate in the competition?

196
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,110
Very well.

197
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,230
Then you may

198
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,400
finish this paper first

199
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:48,520
and give it to me tomorrow.

200
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,710
Ding Xian, are you listening to me?

201
00:12:52,910 --> 00:12:54,030
Yes, I am.

202
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,440
I'll think about it.

203
00:12:55,590 --> 00:12:56,400
Well,

204
00:12:57,230 --> 00:12:58,030
don't

205
00:12:58,230 --> 00:13:00,640
do anything irrelevant to Chinese in my class.

206
00:13:12,670 --> 00:13:13,880
Did our Chinese teacher criticize you?

207
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:17,550
Not really.

208
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:27,470
Zhou Siyue

209
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:33,110
Do you think that girls are more suitable to learn arts courses?

210
00:13:35,760 --> 00:13:37,760
I don't see any connections between them.

211
00:13:38,670 --> 00:13:39,840
Neither do I.

212
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:43,200
But my parents and our Chinese teacher all said

213
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:46,030
that girls should learn arts

214
00:13:46,110 --> 00:13:47,790
and they don't want me to learn science.

215
00:13:51,110 --> 00:13:52,280
Then do you think

216
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:55,520
you are good at arts or science?

217
00:13:58,670 --> 00:14:00,840
On choosing arts or science,

218
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,790
you don't need to care about others' thoughts.

219
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,150
You just

220
00:14:04,350 --> 00:14:05,760
make your own decision on the basis of

221
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,960
your interest.

222
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:13,790
I'll support you no matter what decision you'll make.

223
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:16,030
Really?

224
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,350
Will you support me

225
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:22,110
if I choose arts?

226
00:14:22,910 --> 00:14:24,030
Of course.

227
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:29,670
Forget it.

228
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:32,000
I'll take a nap first.

229
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:48,910
Deng Wanwan, what's wrong with you?

230
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:50,550
He Xingwen, are you the only one who has homework?

231
00:15:50,590 --> 00:15:51,790
I don't have homework?

232
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:52,910
Don't you feel embarrassed

233
00:15:53,110 --> 00:15:54,400
to make me do the cleaning

234
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,400
outside alone?

235
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:56,910
No one force you to do so.

236
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:58,840
And it's my own business to do it or not.

237
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,710
I'm busy preparing for the math competition

238
00:16:01,350 --> 00:16:02,320
and have no spare time.

239
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:03,840
Don't be mad.

240
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:04,910
He Xingwen

241
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,280
How could you say that?

242
00:16:08,150 --> 00:16:09,550
Zhou Siyue also participates in the competition.

243
00:16:09,710 --> 00:16:11,230
And he never takes it as an excuse.

244
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,640
No wonder Mr. Liu likes him,

245
00:16:12,790 --> 00:16:14,000
not you.

246
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:17,200
Everyone knows that you like Zhou Siyue.

247
00:16:18,350 --> 00:16:19,640
What are you saying?

248
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:20,910
It's ridiculous.

249
00:16:21,110 --> 00:16:22,640
Mr. Liu treats him so well just like his own son.

250
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,670
Maybe he will be recommended for admission to college.

251
00:16:24,840 --> 00:16:26,080
He's the future student of top university.

252
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,350
I can't afford to offend him.

253
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:37,150
He Xingwen

254
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:40,110
I used to think that you're able to go to top university, too.

255
00:16:40,790 --> 00:16:42,000
But now,

256
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:43,150
I think you can just go to an

257
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:45,080
ordinary college at most.

258
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,350
You can just mind your own business.

259
00:16:47,520 --> 00:16:49,590
Why do you judge others like that?

260
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:52,910
If my friend can be recommended for admission to a prestigious university,

261
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:55,550
I'll be happy for him.

262
00:16:57,440 --> 00:16:58,000
Yeah.

263
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,790
This is just sour grapes.

264
00:17:00,110 --> 00:17:02,150
It's dangerous to have thoughts like this.

265
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:14,760
Not bad.

266
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,589
Our good girl knows how to lash out at somebody.

267
00:17:20,829 --> 00:17:22,950
Thanks to you.

268
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,160
Silly girl.

269
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:33,430
Zhou Siyue

270
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,190
Actually, I'm not silly.

271
00:17:57,470 --> 00:17:58,470
I know.

272
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:13,640
12 to 12.

273
00:18:17,230 --> 00:18:18,350
You did scare me when

274
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:19,590
you lashed out at He Xingwen.

275
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,280
You are so brave!

276
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,470
I didn't think much of it at the time.

277
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:26,070
It's just that He Xingwen was way out of the line.

278
00:18:26,880 --> 00:18:29,070
You begin to defend Zhou Siyue, now.

279
00:18:30,310 --> 00:18:32,070
13 to 12.

280
00:18:35,430 --> 00:18:37,950
Do you remember last time Mr. Liu said I violated the rules?

281
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,590
He was the first one that

282
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,070
defended me since I came to this city.

283
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:43,830
So now,

